OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1771938194
OL,3,CNew Zealand would support removal of
OL,4,CAndrew from line of succession
OL,6,FA spokesperson for Christopher Luxon,
OL,7,Fthe country's prime minister, said:
OL,8,F"If the UK Government proposes to
OL,9,Fremove Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor from
OL,10,Fthe order of succession, New Zealand
OL,11,Fwould support it.
OL,13,F"The UK Government has said any
OL,14,Fproposals would come after the police
OL,15,Finvestigation concludes."
OL,17,FNew Zealand's backing comes after
OL,18,FAustralia's Prime Minister wrote to
OL,19,FSir Keir Starmer saying his government
OL,20,Fwould support "any proposal" to remove
OL,21,FAndrew from the line of succession.
OL,26,@pD@AOUuD@AOUwD@YO]|D@OOU|D@\O]
