OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1771938194
OL,3,CNew Zealand would support removal of
OL,4,CAndrew from line of succession
OL,6,F"There's also a much broader principle
OL,7,Fat stake here. No one, regardless of
OL,8,Ftheir title or their friends, should
OL,9,Fbe beyond the scrutiny of Parliament.
OL,11,F"It is time to end the age of
OL,12,Fimpunity, scrap rules that stifle
OL,13,Fscrutiny or debate, and ensure that
OL,14,Feveryone in public office ` no matter
OL,15,Fhow powerful ` can be held properly to
OL,16,Faccount."
OL,18,FAndrew has denied any wrongdoing over
OL,19,Fhis links to the convicted sex
OL,20,Foffender, but has not directly
OL,21,Fresponded to the latest allegations.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUxD@IO]
